Perfect! I have found all the regulations/法规 feature code. Here's my complete report:

## Regulations Feature - Code Locations and Implementation

### 1. HTML Structure (index.html, lines 248-260)

```html
<!-- 法规库弹窗 -->
<div class="modal" id="lawModal">
    <div class="modal-content glass-card" style="max-width:650px;max-height:80vh;overflow-y:auto">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <h2>⚖ 跨国法规库</h2>
            <button class="popup-close" id="lawModalClose">✕</button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:12px;flex-wrap:wrap" id="lawCountryBtns"></div>
            <div id="lawItems"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```

**Button trigger** (line 32):
```html
<button class="btn btn-small" id="lawBtn">⚖ 法规</button>
```

### 2. JavaScript Implementation (renderer.js, lines 1260-1304)

**Modal initialization and button handler** (lines 1260-1264):
```javascript
const lawModal = document.getElementById('lawModal');
document.getElementById('lawBtn').addEventListener('click', () => { lawModal.classList.add('show'); loadRegulations(); });
document.getElementById('lawModalClose').addEventListener('click', () => lawModal.classList.remove('show'));
lawModal.addEventListener('click', (e) => { if (e.target === lawModal) lawModal.classList.remove('show'); });
```

**Load regulations data** (lines 1266-1285):
```javascript
let regulationsData = null;
async function loadRegulations() {
  if (!regulationsData) regulationsData = await ipcRenderer.invoke('get-regulations');
  const btns = document.getElementById('lawCountryBtns');
  if (btns.children.length) return; // already loaded
  for (const [code, country] of Object.entries(regulationsData)) {
    const btn = document.createElement('button');
    btn.className = 'law-country-btn';
    btn.textContent = country.name;
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      btns.querySelectorAll('.law-country-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
      btn.classList.add('active');
      showLawItems(code);
    });
    btns.appendChild(btn);
  }
  // 默认选第一个
  const first = btns.querySelector('.law-country-btn');
  if (first) first.click();
}
```

**Display regulations items** (lines 1287-1304):
```javascript
function showLawItems(countryCode) {
  const country = regulationsData[countryCode];
  const container = document.getElementById('lawItems');
  container.innerHTML = '';
  for (const item of country.items) {
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'law-item';
    div.innerHTML = `<div class="law-item-title">${item.title} <button class="law-speak-btn">🔊</button></div>
      <div class="law-item-content">${item.content}</div>`;
    div.querySelector('.law-speak-btn').addEventListener('click', () => {
      speechSynthesis.cancel();
      const u = new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(item.content);
      u.lang = country.lang; u.rate = 0.85;
      speechSynthesis.speak(u);
    });
    container.appendChild(div);
  }
}
```

## Summary

**UI Flow:**
1. User clicks "⚖ 法规" button (line 32, index.html)
2. Modal opens and `loadRegulations()` fetches data via IPC
3. Country buttons are dynamically created from `regulationsData` object
4. Clicking a country button calls `showLawItems(countryCode)`
5. Regulations display with title, content, and speak button (🔊)

**Key Features:**
- No add/edit/delete UI - regulations are read-only display
- Country-based filtering with button tabs
- Text-to-speech for each regulation item
- Data fetched from backend via `ipcRenderer.invoke('get-regulations')`
